Algorithm:

1. Input: Two positive integers, a and b.
2. Check: If b is 0, then the GCD is a. Return a.
3. Else, set a = b and b = a % b (remainder of the division of a by b).
4. Repeat the process until b becomes 0.
5. Output: The GCD is the value of a when b becomes 0.

Pseudocode:

GCD(a, b):
    while b â‰  0:
        temp = b
        b = a % b
        a = temp
    return a

    Flow Chart :
    
    Start[Start] --> Input[Input a and b]
    Input --> Check{Check if b = 0}
    Check -->|Yes| Output[Output a]
    Check -->|No| Calculate[Calculate a % b]
    Calculate --> Update[Update a = b and b = remainder]
    Update --> Check
    Output --> End[End]
